Prevalence and Characteristics of Adrenal Tumors in an Unselected Screening Population : A Cross-Sectional Study.
 The prevalence of adrenal tumors in the general adult screening population is 1.4%, and most of these tumors are nonfunctioning regardless of patient age. Cortisol and aldosterone secretion are the main causes of functional adenomas. Primary funding source National Key Research and Development Program of China and National Natural Science Foundation of China.
